{"id":14880959,"mediaExerciseId":"fa86ca2b-4b0a-407c-ab9b-795895a2b1ff","exerciseName":"21","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612301,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":185,"solutions":[{"id":6347671,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will solve or the number of months before a loan is paid off using the concept of present value annuity.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The present value annuity refers to the current value of future payments based on the different rates that are given. We will use this concept to solve for the number of months before a loan is paid off. The formula that we will use is:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Present value annuity}&=\\text{Payment} \\times\\dfrac{1-\\left(\\frac{1}{(1+\\text{rate})^\\text{time}}\\right)}{\\text{rate}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Substituting the values, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\$18,000&=\\$450 \\times\\dfrac{1-\\left(\\frac{1}{(1+0.013)^\\text{time}}\\right)}{0.013}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Simplify the formula to get this:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\dfrac{1}{1.013^\\text{time}}&=1-\\left(\\dfrac{\\$18,000}{\\$450}\\times0.013\\right)\\\\\n\\dfrac{1}{1.013^\\text{time}}&=0.48\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Simplifying further, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n1.013^\\text{time}&=\\dfrac{1}{0.48}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nUsing the law of logarithms, we can set up the formula as:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{time}&=\\dfrac{\\log 2.083}{\\log 1.013}\\\\[15 pt]\n&=56.81\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThis means that at this rate, the given loan will be paid back in $56.81$ months which is equal to $4.73$ years","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"8319b67d-cd3b-4e41-8335-0d760e7f4381","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880960,"exerciseName":"22","page":185,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"32694574-37a2-4ac5-9a12-38830cd0fb7c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-22-32694574-37a2-4ac5-9a12-38830cd0fb7c"},{"id":14880961,"exerciseName":"23","page":185,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"aa712b1d-0e4d-4ebc-bc0b-5a092ac270cf","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-23-aa712b1d-0e4d-4ebc-bc0b-5a092ac270cf"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880958,"exerciseName":"20","page":185,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b5b87314-1316-4da7-82b2-e3d0aa786ee1","_webUrl":"http